@siretart ping - On SID, it seems installing the `podman` package doesn't bring in all necessary dependencies.  Debian SID [CI VM Image build-log](https://cirrus-ci.com/task/5019989619507200) shows it only installs netavark and not aardvark-dns.  [The script that sets up the image](https://github.com/containers/automation_images/pull/250/files#diff-727e9289c12e01646bb49f30cb044cfcdf752a05d2137b49235a1a7bcd77da8d) mentions 'podman' and assumes that will haul in everything necessary.  Is this an incorrect assumption for Debian?

The `netavark` and `aardvark-dns` packages should be basically locked-together-at-the-hip together.  They should always be installed together, with matching versions.  Podman won't work without both, or the alternative `containernetworking-plugins`.

Can you help fix this or is there some packaging policy I'm misunderstanding for Debian?
